2ï¸âƒ£ Different Types of Testing (Overview)
Testing can be classified based on levels & purpose.

3ï¸âƒ£ Integration Testing
What is Integration Testing?
Integration testing checks:
Whether modules work correctly when combined.

Why Needed?
Individual modules may work fine
Errors occur when they interact

Types of Integration Testing:
ğŸ”¹ Top-Down
Main module tested first
Sub-modules added later
Uses stubs

ğŸ”¹ Bottom-Up
Low-level modules tested first
Uses drivers

ğŸ”¹ Big Bang
All modules integrated at once
Hard to debug

ğŸ“Œ Example:
Login module + Database module + Dashboard module.

4ï¸âƒ£ System Testing
What is System Testing?
System testing checks:
The complete system as a whole against requirements.

Who Performs It?

ğŸ‘‰ Testers (QA team)
Types under System Testing:
Functional testing
Performance testing
Security testing
Usability testing

ğŸ“Œ Example:
Testing an entire e-commerce website before release.

ğŸ§  Exam Line:
System testing is done after integration testing.

5ï¸âƒ£ User Acceptance Testing (UAT)
What is UAT?
UAT is performed to:
Verify the software is acceptable to the end user/client.

Who Performs UAT?
Client
Business users
End users

When?
After system testing
Before production release

ğŸ“Œ Example:
Client checks whether billing system meets business needs.

ğŸ§  Important:
If UAT fails â†’ software is NOT released.

